  "text": "Thus, the difficulty to functionally integrate specific imported tRNAs into the mitochondrial translation system represents a barrier for mitochondrial tRNA gene loss. Translation initiation and mitochondrial codon reassignments appear to be especially strong handicaps for imported tRNAs. Surprisingly, however, two taxonomic groups, trypanosomatids [CITATION_1] ) and apicomplexans [CITATION_2] CrausazEsseiva et al. 2004b) , have lost all mitochondrial tRNA genes, indicating that these barriers are not absolute (see below).",
